         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... stands. This believer [is] Sirmir (?).</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="philcomment">Transliteration by <bibl><title corresp="ref:ogihara2014"/><citedRange>121</citedRange></bibl>, translation based on him. The language of the first caption is unclear, the second is clearly TA. Ogihara compares the name to the Chinese proper name <hi>Sirmir</hi> attested in Uyghur documents (as per p.c. by Prof. Matsui and Dr. Kitsudo).</note><note type="remarks">Two captions above a wall painting labeled "Tocharian Donors in Black Hats" on exhibition in the Hermitage Museum, St. Petersburg (<bibl><title corresp="ref:ogihara2014"/><citedRange>120, fn. 21</citedRange></bibl>).</note><note type="remarks">The press mark used here is provisorial.</note></p>
         </div>
